## 6. Security Decisions Made

-   No ICS private link sharing
-   No direct main calendar OAuth to OpenClaw
-   Burner account isolation
-   Dedicated buffer calendar
-   Future-only sync window
-   Manual monthly audit reminder
-   Upsert instead of insert (no runaway duplication)
-   Limited Google scopes

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 7. Automation Cadence

Cron schedule:

`0 */6 * * *`

Runs every 6 hours.

Low frequency chosen intentionally because: - Personal calendar - Not
time-sensitive - Reduces API calls - Lower surface area

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 8. Data Exposure Model

OpenClaw will see: - Category - Duration - Time block

OpenClaw will NOT see: - Event titles - Notes - Locations - Attendees -
Sensitive details

Details can be selectively provided manually when desired.

